      "span_text": "The reason we measure algorithm performance as a function of the Chimera size and not the number of qubits is that problem difficulty tends to scale exponentially with the Chimera size, i.e., with the square root of the number of qubits, since the treewidth of a Chimera graph C s is linear in s  .",
